							<div class="comment" id="c6142">
								<p>I'm a purist, too, when it comes to guac (fellow Texan here!), but your recipe is fairly similar to mine, although I add garlic to taste, and cumin, and WHITE pepper, which I think has a better flavor.  (Though, admittedly, it may just be an appearance preference.)  Also, as for keeping the guac green in the fridge, along with putting the pit back in, instead of putting it in a tupperware container with air inevitably at the top, try either putting it into a zip-seal baggie and pressing out all the air, or putting a layer of plastic wrap directly touching the entire top surface of the bowl of guac (air being what makes the avocado go brown quickly).</p>	
