							<div class="comment odd" id="c29969">
								<p>Your recipe closely resembles what I had in Northern Mexico as a child. One common addition is a teaspoon or so of Knorr Suissa Caldo de Pollo, a powdered chicken bouillon used ubiquitously in Mexico. Also, I use key limes, which again are much more common in Mexico than lemons.</p>

<p>Regarding testing for ripeness, an elderly gentleman in a grocery store once showed me a trick for testing avocados that doesn't damage them in the way that poking at them does. He said to gently test the stem and see if it wiggled. If so, the avocado is ready to eat. It has never failed me...and it's also a good way to tell if they are overripe. If that is the case, the stem will be completely wobbly and possibly break off.</p>	
							</div>
