							<div class="comment odd" id="c60881">
								<p>Austin, Texas, here:</p>

<p>I agree, use the best avocados, go easy on the salt, use white onion instead of red (you really don't have to use tomatoes, but if you do, add only at the last minute, sparingly and drained of juice).  </p>

<p>My 'secret' ingredient, besides the onion, is a dollop of mayonnaise (never Miracle Whip).  How much depends on how large a batch of guacamole you're making: it gives a texture and sheen that people can't identify, but love.</p>	
